# Legacy URL map — Speedy Gonzalez Roofing (build spec §10)
#
# Source of truth: the 84 URLs crawled from the live Duda site
# (.firecrawl/speedy-map.json). Every one of them resolves to a 200 or a 301
# here — scripts/linkcheck.js asserts that against this file and fails the build
# if a legacy URL is dropped or points at a page that no longer exists.
#
# Cloudflare Pages matches top to bottom, first match wins — AND it evaluates
# this file before serving static assets. A rule whose path matches a real page
# therefore takes that page off the site. There are no splats here for exactly
# that reason; see the service-areas section.
#
# Host + protocol canonicalization (http->https, non-www->www) is handled by a
# Cloudflare Redirect Rule, not here — _redirects can't match on hostname.

